  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Avocado Wild West Salad</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Microwave</cat>
        <cat>Salads</cat></categories>
      <yield>6</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>medium</unit></amt>
        <item>Onion</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Tomatoes</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Head lettuce</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Grated Cheddar cheese</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>French or Thousand Island dressing</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Hot sauce to taste</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Bag corn or tortilla chips; (6 ounce)</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>large</unit></amt>
        <item>Avocado</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>pound</unit></amt>
        <item>Ground beef</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>can</unit></amt>
        <item>Kidney beans; (15 ounce) drained</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Chop the onion, the tomatoes and the head of lettuce. Toss with the cup of
  grated cheese and the dressing, and add the hot sauce to taste. Crunch and
  add the chips. Slice and add the avocado. Crumble ground beef in a 2 quart
  casserole. Microwave at high (100%) 6 to 7 minutes, stirring once to break
  up the beef. Add drained kidney beans and salt. Microwave at medium high
  (70%) 4 minutes, stirring once during cooking time. Mix into the cold
  salad. Makes 6 servings.
  
